-- allium: 3
-- specs/cuda-native-dispatch/calibrated_op_equivalence.allium
--
-- Status: PLACEHOLDER. Bound by PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md
-- commits C8 (MATMUL_STREAM_SPLIT), C9 (REDUCE_CROSS_DEVICE),
-- C10 (PEER_COPY), C11 (GRAPH_CAPTURE). This spec is updated
-- incrementally by each commit; the full multi-op invariant is
-- complete after C11.
--
-- Scope: for every calibrated op registered with the framework,
-- the default and alt strategies produce numerically equivalent
-- output (byte-identical OR fp16/fp32 ULP-bound, per the op's
-- specific contract). The dispatch decision (which strategy fires
-- at a given payload size) may vary across hardware via
-- calibration, but the OUTPUT BITS MUST NOT vary across strategy
-- choices for the same input.
--
-- Why this spec exists: calibration produces a different threshold
-- on different hardware. Without the equivalence contract,
-- threshold variance would propagate to output variance — a
-- determinism gap. The equivalence contract is the SAFETY NET that
-- makes calibration safe to deploy.
--
-- Per-op contracts (composed):
--
--   REDUCE_CROSS_DEVICE:
--     default = cudaMemcpyPeerAsync + element-wise-add kernel
--     alt     = ncclAllReduce
--     Equivalence: byte-identical (PD5 confirmed across 13 shapes
--     from 2 MB to 1.5 GB, n_diff = 0 everywhere).
--
--   MATMUL_STREAM_SPLIT:
--     default = single-stream cublasHgemm
--     alt     = two-stream column-split cublasHgemm + per-stream
--               output assembly
--     Equivalence: fp16 ULP-bound (the column-split changes the
--     cublas K-tile config, which can shift the reduction tree
--     shape; PD6 confirmed byte-identity at 2 of 3 tested shapes,
--     ULP-diff at the third with max_abs_diff = 0.015625 = 1 ULP
--     at the relevant magnitudes).
--
--   PEER_COPY:
--     default = direct cudaMemcpyPeerAsync
--     alt     = staged via pinned-host intermediate
--     Equivalence: byte-identical (both paths preserve byte
--     content; no arithmetic).
--
--   GRAPH_CAPTURE:
--     default = cudaGraphLaunch (captured graph replay)
--     alt     = eager kernel launches with no capture
--     Equivalence: byte-identical (the kernel sequence is the
--     same; only the dispatch mechanism differs).
--
-- Includes:
--   - Per-op default and alt strategy declarations.
--   - Per-op equivalence predicate (byte-identical or ULP-bound,
--     with specific ULP bound named).
--   - Composition contract OutputDoesNotDependOnStrategy — given
--     same input, same hardware, both strategies produce
--     equivalent output regardless of which fires.
--
-- CODE REFS (per-op, post-implementation):
--   C8: ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu mul_mat dispatch
--   C9: ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/reduce.cu cross-device reduce
--   C10: ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu cpy_tensor_async
--   C11: ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda.cu graph_compute
--
-- TBD: fill per-op equivalence contracts incrementally as C8-C11
-- land. The final spec covers all four registered ops.

allium 3

